Which version of the crawler are you using?  If a recent version of 
TRUNK, it was in a borked state for a while over thursday/friday where 
fetches would often fail to get any content (content-size was zero).

Otherwise, for the awkward job of debugging authentications, uncomment 
in the heritrix.properties the following lines:

# Enable the following lines to watch authentications running.
# org.archive.crawler.fetcher.FetchHTTP.level = FINE
# org.archive.crawler.prefetch.PreconditionEnforcer.level = FINE

This will spew more logging around authentication.  It may be sufficent 
for you to figure whats up.  You might also consider browsing and 
crawling via a http debugging proxy such as Charles 
(http://www.xk72.com/charles/) so you can compare the headers being sent 
by the browser and then by Heritrix (Or use ethereal/wireshark).

St.Ack


